<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1944-09-19T03:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1944-09-19T03:00:00-05:00" n="560" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d560">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">740.00119 EW/9–1944: Telegram</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in the Soviet Union</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Harriman</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                </hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Moscow</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-09-19T11:00:00+03:00">September 19, 1944—11 a.m.</date>
                                    <lb/> [Received September 19—6:27 a.m.]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>3571. Vyshinski requested me to call on him in order to inform me
                                that the Finnish armistice<note n="96" xml:id="d560fn96">For a text
                                    of “Conditions of An Armistice with Finland” signed at Moscow,
                                    September 19, 1944, with Annexes and Protocols, see <hi rend="italic">British and Foreign State Papers</hi>, vol.
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">cxlv</hi>, p. 513; also <hi rend="italic">Izvestiya</hi>, September 21, 1944, p.
                                    1.</note> would be signed at noon today, Moscow time. The only
                                substantial change in it is that Finland is given 2½ months to
                                transfer its Army to a peace time status (instead of 2 months as in
                                the original terms) and 6 years to pay the indemnity (instead of 5
                                years).</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Harriman</hi>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>